.DT
set_down_dir
Disk World creator help
set_down_dir

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_down_dir -  This function sets the direction that is considered to be down by this room.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_down_dir(string dir)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^mes%^RESET%^ - the new direction to be considered to be down
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function sets the direction that is considered to be down by this room.
This is used by several exit messages.  Also, dense objects will be inclined
to move in this direction.  The default, of course, is "down".
.EP

.SH Example 1
.SI 5
  set_down_dir("downeast");

.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
query_down_dir, set_sink_in_mess, set_sink_out_mess
.EP

